  "text": "We say that the set of points {x j } r j=1 ⊂ R n has the MNI-property (minimal non-interpolation property) with respect to the {a i } m i=1 , if {x j } r j=1 has the NI-property and no proper subset of the {x j } r j=1 has the NI-property. The following result, to be found in Braess, Pinkus [CITATION_1] , easily follows from the above definitions.",
